descript.abstract: Five-year age/sex group estimates for 2000-2010 for subnational areas of Haiti were prepared by the U.S. Census Bureau and linked as attribute data to boundary shapefiles. The estimates, based on the most recent available census data, are consistent with the midyear national projections from the International Data Base of the Census Bureau.
descript.purpose: The U.S. Census Bureau is providing subnational population group estimates in a geographic information system (GIS) for users of the President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR) Spatial Data Repository. Ranging in a time series from the recent past to the near future, users can use these population estimates for analyses and other applications regarding the patterns of HIV indicators within a country in a spatial context, and can depict the results graphically.
